wiki.summary: "Kings & Queens" is a song by Ava Max, released as a single from her debut album "Heaven & Hell" on March 12, 2020. The song includes a credited interpolation of "If You Were a Woman (And I Was a Man)" by Bonnie Tyler. "Kings & Queens" received generally favorable reception from critics, who praised the production, guitar solo, and lyricism. The music video was released on March 27, 2020, and features a Khaleesi inspired Ava dancing in a heaven-themed throne room alongside a group of dancers, while also feasting at a banquet. Read more on Last.fm.
